  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-10-07",
    "date": "2004-10-25T18:25:28Z",
    "text": "Assistance for Orphans and Other Vulnerable Children in Developing Countries Act of 2004 - Amends the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to authorize the President to provide assistance, including through nongovernmental or international organizations, for basic care for orphans and other vulnerable children in developing countries, including assistance for: (1) community-based care; (2) school food programs; (3) education and employment training; (4) mental health care; (5) protection of inheritance rights; and (6) HIV/AIDS care.\n\nDirects the President to develop a coordinating strategy for such assistance."
  },
